TASK_TITLE=Fix: workers must never overwrite report files — append only
TASK_STATUS=pending_user_confirmation
TASK_TYPE=bug
TASK_CREATED_BY=boss
TASK_TEAM=W4
TASK_DESCRIPTION=A worker on task 492 used Write() on a report file and removed 196 lines of prior research, replacing it with a 32-line verification report. Reports at /tmp/doey/doey/reports/*.report must be append-only — new sections get added, old content is never deleted. This is a behavioral issue in the worker agent template and possibly the Subtaskmaster dispatch instructions. Fix: (1) Add append-only rule to doey-worker.md.tmpl for report files (2) Add guard in on-pre-tool-use.sh that blocks Write on existing .report files (only Edit or append allowed) (3) Subtaskmaster template should instruct workers to append verification results, not overwrite research.
TASK_SUBTASKS=1:W4.1: Research current on-pre-tool-use.sh Write guards, doey-worker.md.tmpl report handling rules, and doey-subtaskmaster.md.tmpl verification dispatch instructions:done\n2:W4.2: Implement append-only guard in on-pre-tool-use.sh, add rule to doey-worker.md.tmpl, add instruction to doey-subtaskmaster.md.tmpl, run expand-templates.sh and test-bash-compat.sh:done\n3:W4.1: Verify append-only guard — test that Write on existing .report file is blocked, Edit is allowed, and new .report Write is allowed:done
